          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Expansion threats and backlash
</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-9-1.jpg" alt="Expansion threats and backlash" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Donald Trump's recent claims have shown his desire to deploy an expansionist design. His comments on using military forces to press for territorial claims last month have received strong reactions. Following Trump's claims that China controls the Panama Canal, Foreign Minister Javier Martinez-Acha <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-09-01-2025-h1-1-dismissed-the-comments" target="_blank">dismissed the comments</a> as "nonsense" and asserted that Panama operates the canal solely.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Justin Trudeau hit back at Trump's suggestion of a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-09-01-2025-h1-2-canada-us-merger" target="_blank">Canada-US merger</a>, saying, "There isn't a snowball's chance in heel’. French Foreign Minister Jean-Noel Barrot warned Trump against the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-09-01-2025-h1-3-eu-sovereignity-threat" target="_blank">EU sovereignty threat</a> after Trump refused to rule out military action to take Greenland. Barrot asserted that the EU would defend its borders.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Experts claim that Trump’s expansionism is a result of him emboldened by the election result and the rise of far-right leaders in the world. He is pushing to demonstrate that the US is the greatest power in the world, and his expansion ideas mimic old-school war-making tactics of occupation and annexure of territory, this time for energy independence.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

