          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇹🇭 Thailand: Lim Kimya killer arrested</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The suspected killer of former Cambodian opposition lawmaker Lim Kimya, who was shot dead in Bangkok on Tuesday, has been arrested in Cambodia. The suspect, a 41-year-old Thai national, fled to Cambodia after the attack, and Thai authorities are seeking his extradition. Lim Kimya, a member of the dissolved Cambodia National Rescue Party, was shot three times in a brash attack. Bryony Lau of Human Rights Watch in Asia has called for <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-09-01-2025-br1-9-a-complete-investigation" target="_blank">a complete investigation</a>, while the Cambodian government denies involvement. The motive behind the killing remains unclear, and the investigation is ongoing.</p>
        </mj-text>
