          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇬🇭 Ghana: John Mahama returns as president</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">John Mahama was sworn in as Ghana’s president for a third term on Tuesday, following his victory in the December election. Thousands of people attended his inauguration. His term comes as Ghana is dealing with its <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-09-01-2025-br2-10-worst-economic-crisis" target="_blank">worst economic crisis</a> in decades. Mahama, who was president from 2012 to 2017, promised to tackle significant issues such as corruption, stabilize the economy, and create jobs. The election was conducted amid economic turmoil and was praised for its peaceful process.</p>
        </mj-text>
